      "content": "This proposal aims to accelerate Pennsylvania's shift toward renewable energy by expanding solar subsidies while reducing support for coal, which could lower long-term environmental damage and future climate risks. Proponents argue this investment will boost local jobs in green tech and improve grid resilience against extreme weather, whereas opponents warn it might increase short-term costs for households already struggling with rising energy prices. Additionally, coal industry workers face significant unemployment risks without adequate transition programs, and critics suggest the state should first ensure energy affordability for all families before heavily subsidizing new projects.",
