      "content": "You're right that global trends away from fossil fuels are clear, but the argument isn't just about inevitability—it's about ensuring a just transition so workers aren't left behind during the shift. Critics also question whether removing subsidies without providing alternative jobs or retraining programs could unfairly hurt vulnerable communities that depend on the coal industry. Ultimately, the debate often centers on balancing long-term environmental goals with the immediate human and economic impacts on those directly affected by industrial changes.",
      "source": "target",
